<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/12584060-crystal-chow"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1383637037i/12584060._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/12584060-crystal-chow">Crystal Chow</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Therano is mentioned explicitly in the description of the book so I don&apos;t think the choice of title has anything to do with legal issues. The point is<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Therano is mentioned explicitly in the description of the book so I don't think the choice of title has anything to do with legal issues. The point is that Theranos isn't simply an outlier in the Silicon Valley but an epitome of the often overhyped startup culture that idolizes entrepreneurs and self-made billionaires. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
